{
  "stem": "26609.18",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we know she was in my place, she was in other places where he sent her around from place to place to get her nourished a little, you know, to-- because even after the war, it wasn't food, straightaway, enough.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he sent her from home-- she remembers it, she told me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She remembers when she was in that orphanage-- and it's another story-- that they didn't have trained staff to work in orphanage with little children.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was a girl without-- because born just before the war, she didn't attend even school at all, even not primary, and a stupid girl, and she was as the head of that orphanage, a young girl about 18.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she said-- she took us for-- for a walk out on the street, and because it was after the war that she taught us [NON-ENGLISH] to sing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's the Jewish hymn, [NON-ENGLISH], you know?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she said, and we went out on the street and there was a chair, so I sang, [SINGING] [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she came up to me and hit me in my face, a little child, survived.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because there's-- I said, why did you do that?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You cross yourself?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because you see, Mommy-- she said later when I found her-- because [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Chocha-- ?] the Polish woman who kept her was [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Chocha-- ?] taught me if I see [NON-ENGLISH], God will be angry with me that I don't cross myself.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she taught us to sing a Jewish song, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know what [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I sang, [SINGING] [NON-ENGLISH] to be sure, sure that not one God will hurt me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I--I--I sang [NON-ENGLISH] and I crossed myself because there was a church.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
